Generic single-database configuration.

rm alembic/versions/*.py
rm job_portal.db
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "init tables"
alembic upgrade head

Alembic helps you manage database changes safely and systematically over time

Problem Without Alembic
Imagine this situation:
Day 1:
class User(Base):
    name = Column(String)
Day 10:
class User(Base):
    name = Column(String)
    email = Column(String)
    
👉 Now what?
❌ Your database still doesn’t have email column
❌ Your app breaks
❌ You manually alter DB → risky & inconsistent

✅ Solution: Alembic
Alembic tracks changes like:
Version 1 → create users table
Version 2 → add email column
Version 3 → add jobs table
👉 It acts like Git for your database

Core Purpose
Purpose	Explanation
Version Control	Tracks DB schema changes
Consistency	Same DB structure across all environments
Automation	No manual SQL needed
Rollback	Undo changes safely